//axhob_operation
{bust_handbook_jurisdiction_top}

NOTE: Top-level landing surface for the {bus_jurisdiction} handbook.
Renders handbook prose to the operator's terminal as the entry point
into bootstrap, garrison, and dispatch procedures.
No remote contact and no profile mutation.

//axhos_step
. *Render landing*: emit the jurisdiction handbook landing content,
including pointers to the admin SSH bootstrap procedure (operator-
manual prerequisite to {busn_garrison}), the per-shell-letter
garrison tabtargets, and the workload dispatch tabtargets.

//axhog_guarantee
No remote contact occurred and no local file was written.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 after the landing content is printed.
Non-zero only when the handbook content cannot be located or rendered.

= Bash Utilities Specification
:doctype: book

// tag::mapping-section[]
//
// Category declarations:
// bust_:  Tabtarget (launcher naming vesture)
// busd:   Dispatch (non-terminal, tabtarget system umbrella)
// busdc_: Dispatch Colophon (routing identifier)
// busdf_: Dispatch Frontispiece (human-readable description)
// busdi_: Dispatch Imprint (embedded parameter/target specifier)
// busdm_: Dispatch Formulary (routing component)
// busdl_: Dispatch Launcher (bootstrap script)
// bukro_: Kit Regime Operation (kindle/validate/render)
// burc_:  Configuration Regime (project-level settings)
// burn_:  Node Regime (per-node SSH connection profiles, multi-instance)
// burs_:  Station Regime (developer-level settings)
// burd_:  Dispatch Runtime (ephemeral state assembled during dispatch)
// bure_:  Environment Regime (ambient caller-supplied behavioral overrides)
// busi:   Invocation (test invocation umbrella)
// busn_:  Node Access (verbs for remote node management)
// busit_: Invocation Tier (tier classification)
// busig_: Invocation Global (capture state set by zbuto_invoke)
// busx_:  Case Boundary (test case isolation runner)
// busff_: Fact-File (inter-step communication via output files)
// buf_:   Fact Module (dual-write fact-file primitives)
// busy_:  Yelp (pre-rendered formatted string capture)
// burx_:  Exchange Regime (cross-project dispatch state)
//
// Variant patterns:
//   _s: plural form
//   _p: possessive form
//

// Tabtarget Vesture
:bust_tabtarget:        <<bust_tabtarget,Tabtarget Vesture>>

// Jurisdiction Tabtargets
:bust_fenestrate:                  <<bust_fenestrate,Fenestrate>>
:bust_garrison_bash:               <<bust_garrison_bash,Garrison Bash>>
:bust_garrison_cygwin:             <<bust_garrison_cygwin,Garrison Cygwin>>
:bust_garrison_wsl:                <<bust_garrison_wsl,Garrison WSL>>
:bust_knock:                       <<bust_knock,Knock>>
:bust_command_file:                <<bust_command_file,Command File>>
:bust_interactive_session:         <<bust_interactive_session,Interactive Session>>
:bust_handbook_jurisdiction_top:   <<bust_handbook_jurisdiction_top,Handbook Jurisdiction Top>>

// Regime Config Tabtargets
:bust_node_regime_list:            <<bust_node_regime_list,Node Regime List>>
:bust_node_regime_render:          <<bust_node_regime_render,Node Regime Render>>
:bust_node_regime_validate:        <<bust_node_regime_validate,Node Regime Validate>>
:bust_privilege_regime_list:       <<bust_privilege_regime_list,Privilege Regime List>>
:bust_privilege_regime_render:     <<bust_privilege_regime_render,Privilege Regime Render>>
:bust_privilege_regime_validate:   <<bust_privilege_regime_validate,Privilege Regime Validate>>

// Input Artifacts
:busi_scribed_command_file:  <<busi_scribed_command_file,Scribed Command File>>

// Dispatch
:busdc_colophon:        <<busdc_colophon,Colophon>>

